102 #if defined(_WIN32)
103 
104 /*
105  * GLEW does not include <windows.h> to avoid name space pollution.
106  * GL needs GLAPI and GLAPIENTRY, GLU needs APIENTRY, CALLBACK, and wchar_t
107  * defined properly.
108  */
109 /* <windef.h> */
110 #ifndef APIENTRY
111 #define GLEW_APIENTRY_DEFINED
112 # if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
113 # define APIENTRY __stdcall
114 # elif (_MSC_VER >= 800) || defined(_STDCALL_SUPPORTED) || defined(__BORLANDC__)
115 # define APIENTRY __stdcall
116 # else
117 # define APIENTRY
118 # endif
119 #endif
120 #ifndef GLAPI
121 # if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
122 # define GLAPI extern
123 # endif
124 #endif
125 /* <winnt.h> */
126 #ifndef CALLBACK
127 #define GLEW_CALLBACK_DEFINED
128 # if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
129 # define CALLBACK __attribute__ ((__stdcall__))
130 # elif (defined(_M_MRX000) || defined(_M_IX86) || defined(_M_ALPHA) || defined(_M_PPC)) && !defined(MIDL_PASS)
131 # define CALLBACK __stdcall
132 # else
133 # define CALLBACK
134 # endif
135 #endif
136 /* <wingdi.h> and <winnt.h> */
137 #ifndef WINGDIAPI
138 #define GLEW_WINGDIAPI_DEFINED
139 #define WINGDIAPI __declspec(dllimport)
140 #endif
141 /* <ctype.h> */
142 #if (defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__BORLANDC__)) && !defined(_WCHAR_T_DEFINED)
143 typedef unsigned short wchar_t;
144 # define _WCHAR_T_DEFINED
145 #endif
146 /* <stddef.h> */
147 #if !defined(_W64)
148 # if !defined(__midl) && (defined(_X86_) || defined(_M_IX86)) && defined(_MSC_VER) && _MSC_VER >= 1300
149 # define _W64 __w64
150 # else
151 # define _W64
152 # endif
153 #endif
154 #if !defined(_PTRDIFF_T_DEFINED) && !defined(_PTRDIFF_T_)
155 # ifdef _WIN64
156 //typedef __int64 ptrdiff_t;
157 typedef long int ptrdiff_t;
158 # else
159 typedef _W64 int ptrdiff_t;
160 # endif
161 # define _PTRDIFF_T_DEFINED
162 # define _PTRDIFF_T_
163 #endif
164 
165 #ifndef GLAPI
166 # if defined(__MINGW32__) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
167 # define GLAPI extern
168 # else
169 # define GLAPI WINGDIAPI
170 # endif
171 #endif
172 
173 #ifndef GLAPIENTRY
174 #define GLAPIENTRY APIENTRY
175 #endif
176 
177 /*
178  * GLEW_STATIC needs to be set when using the static version.
179  * GLEW_BUILD is set when building the DLL version.
180  */
181 #ifdef GLEW_STATIC
182 # define GLEWAPI extern
183 #else
184 # ifdef GLEW_BUILD
185 # define GLEWAPI extern __declspec(dllexport)
186 # else
187 # define GLEWAPI extern __declspec(dllimport)
188 # endif
189 #endif
190 
191 #else /* _UNIX */
192 
193 /*
194  * Needed for ptrdiff_t in turn needed by VBO. This is defined by ISO
195  * C. On my system, this amounts to _3 lines_ of included code, all of
196  * them pretty much harmless. If you know of a way of detecting 32 vs
197  * 64 _targets_ at compile time you are free to replace this with
198  * something that's portable. For now, _this_ is the portable solution.
199  * (mem, 2004-01-04)
200  */
201 
202 #include <stddef.h>
203 
204 /* SGI MIPSPro doesn't like stdint.h in C++ mode */
205 
206 #if defined(__sgi) && !defined(__GNUC__)
207 #include <inttypes.h>
208 #else
209 #include <stdint.h>
210 #endif
211 
212 #define GLEW_APIENTRY_DEFINED
213 #define APIENTRY
214 #define GLEWAPI extern

221 #define GLAPIENTRY

223 
224 #endif /* _WIN32 */
